div.h2: Protected Mode Transition: Instruction-Level Sequence Diagram

p.em: x86 real mode protected mode choreography with hardware constraints

div.p: CRITICAL WINDOW CPU is in protected mode but CS=0x0000 (real-mode segment value). No interrupt can fire (cli). Must execute far jmp immediately no other instructions.
Without this step: DS/ES/SS still hold real-mode values (0x0000). First data access CPU misinterprets as selector 0 GPF (null descriptor fault).

ul.li: DS = ES = FS = GS = SS = 0x10 (kernel data)
GDT: 5 entries at known physical address
No IDT yet interrupts must stay disabled

text.tspan: (CPU knows GDT location; still real mode)
Step 4: mov eax, cr0 / or eax,1 / mov cr0,eax
Pipeline flushed again; protected mode stable
CS=0x08 loaded CPU looks up GDT[1]
Code fetches now validated by GDT
Step 6: Load all data segment registers
ESP top of 16KB static kernel stack
